//We have a box of numbers. One number is repeated, and we want to find it.

ğŸ‘£ We have two kids: Slow and Fast.
They both start from the first number in the box.

ğŸš¶â€â™‚ï¸ Slow takes 1 step each time.
ğŸƒâ€â™‚ï¸ Fast takes 2 steps each time.
Theyâ€™re running around the numbers like a circle (because there's a duplicate, so it's like a loop!).

ğŸ‰ When Slow and Fast meet at the same number, we stop!
That means we found the loop where the repeated number hides.

ğŸ‘¦ Now, a third kid, Slow2, starts again from the beginning.

ğŸš¶â€â™‚ï¸ğŸš¶â€â™‚ï¸ Slow and Slow2 now walk slowly (1 step at a time).
They will meet at the magic number â€” the duplicate one!

ğŸ¯ Return the number where they met â€” thatâ€™s the duplicate number!//

class Solution {
    public int findDuplicate(int[] nums) {
        int slow= nums[0];
        int fast= nums[0];

        while(true){
            slow= nums[slow];
            fast=nums[nums[fast]];

            if(slow==fast){
                break;
            }
        }
        int slow2=nums[0];
        while(slow!=slow2){
            slow=nums[slow];
            slow2= nums[slow2];
        }
        return slow;
    }
}

OR

class Solution {
    public int findDuplicate(int[] nums) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int count =0;
        int i=0;
        int j=i+1;
        while(i<nums.length){
            if(nums[i]==nums[j]){
               count= nums[i];
                break;
            }
                i++;
                j++;

        }
        return count;
        
    }
}
